Paper: hep-th/9902193

Date: 1999-02-25

Title: Free Fermions at Finite Temperature

Non-Commutative AlgebraAuthors: S. M. de Souza, O. Rojas Santos, M. T. Thomaz

Comments: 14 pages, no figures

Charret et. al. applied the properties of the Grassmann generators to developa new method to calculate the coefficients of the high temperature expansionof the grand canonical partition function of self-interacting fermionic modelsin any d-dimensions (d>=1). The method explores the anti-commuting nature offermionic fields and avoids the calculation of the fermionic path integral. Weapply this new method to the relativistic free Dirac fermions and recover theknown results in the literature.